thread.title: Donald Trump appears to lose Kanye West's support as rapper deletes tweets about meeting
thread.title_full: Donald Trump appears to lose Kanye West's support as rapper deletes tweets about meeting

author: Our Foreign Staff
title: Donald Trump appears to lose Kanye West's support as rapper deletes tweets about meeting
text:
K anye West, one of Donald Trump's biggest celebrity supporters , appears to have deleted his tweets about his meeting last year with the then US president-elect in which the two discussed multicultural issues.
The influential rapper's handful of Twitter entries from their December 13 meeting at Trump Tower in New York , where West said he had wanted to discuss "bullying, supporting teachers, modernising curriculums and violence in Chicago," were missing from his account on Monday.
After the meeting, West had also tweeted that he felt it "important to have a direct line of communication with our future president if we truly want change".
Profile | Kanye West H e had also posted a picture of a copy of Time Magazine, which had announced the then president-elect as Person Of The Year. Mr Trump had signed it, writing: "To Kanye, you are a great friend. Thanks, Donald Trump".
At the time, a Trump spokesperson told the Daily Beast their meeting was about Mr Trump being a "President for all Americans".
West, 39, emerged as one of Mr Trump's most high-profile supporters during the 2016 election campaign. He made headlines in November when he was booed at a concert for declaring his support for Mr Trump , although he said he had not voted in the presidential election.
